review_blob: Poured from a can to a glass. The pour was clear amber with a one finger head. The aroma was mostly pineapple, tangerine, mango. The taste was lighter than expected given the aroma. Tropical fruits, some grapefruit, light grassy notes, and a hint of butter. The mouthfeel was average and it had a bitter finish that didnt linger.
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: As far as the brewers deScription, Id say it fell a little short. Thats not to say its a bad beer though. The smell has some citrus, mango, and grassy notes. The flavor is grassy and floral with some lemon and a hint of pineapple, but the malt comes through to balance it more than Id expected it to and brings caramel and buttered bread to the mix. If youre looking for a hop explosion, this isnt it. Overall though, its a pretty flavorful beer. The ingredients are quality and it has just enough complexity to keep me wanting more.

The smell was mostly citrus with a very faint bit of malt. Taste was citrus, grapefruit, a little bit of bread, with some lemon at the finish. Medium mouthfeel with not too much carbonation. Overall a really good IPA

What a fantastic IPA! Hops, hops, and more hops. The hops are very prominent but balanced by the honey and not quite overpowering, but close. This beer is packed with flavor, and you really dont notice the ABV until its too late. I dont give the most professional reviews but I can say that this beer is outstanding. Its worth the higher pricetag, but I wish it was available for a larger part of the year.

Has a great aroma, dominated by grapefruit and pine with some slight caramel. The taste is not as hop dominant as I thought it would be. The pine and citrus is strong up front but is balanced out by the malts. The finish is bitter and the hops linger a little. Not a hop bomb but overall a great beer from Sierra Nevada.

It has a nice hoppy smell. The nose is citrus with some carmelly malt sweetness that produces a hint of candy apple. It has a citrusy sweet taste but is balanced by a strong malt backbone. It has a bitter finish without being excessively hoppy. I was hoping for a more dominant hop presence but its still a good beer. I really enjoy Wolverines take on lagers and while I prefer their Gulo Noir, I still find this to be an enjoyable beer with great drinkablilty.

What can I say? If you enjoy hops, you may have found another winner from Founders. It has a great citrusy aroma. It tastes like citrus and grass with light malty notes at the end. It has a bitter finish without being too dry and is surprisingly drinkable. The abv is a little on the high side but not really noticable. Founders proves yet again to really know good beer.
